title: Sidewall, 1868–69
creditline: Gift of the Jefferson County Chapter, Association for the Preservation of Tennessee Antiquities
description: Floral stripe design with alternating wide stripes. One contains a celery-like flower, the other a cone-shaped flower. Printed in brown or deep green on medium brown striped and crosshatched ground.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1868–69. Machine-printed. 
Gift of the Jefferson County Chapter, Association for the Preservation of Tennessee Antiquities. 1971-64-12-a/c.
